Node.Notes: Assumes parenthetical explanatory clause: [They/these] are his father's wives.
Uncertain. GKC 126z accepts this as adjectival to the noun determined by the them suffix, despite the lack of an article before the adjective.
This tunic marked Jacob's special affection for Joseph and served as a perpetual reminder to his brothers.
Uncertain what is special about this tunic/robe. Many-colored depends on LXX and Vulgate. A long garment reaching to the ankles or wrists is guess based on Aramaic cognate.
Either two groups of traders involved (Ismaelites and then Midianites) or only one group of traders involved (Ismaelites and Midianites used in a general sense for related tribes).
